&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://hi-contentful.imgix.net/4xN7JhmwCRuz3y9M8L8CF7/5c244c52cfc982bd1a348a80dc35d43b/hi-logo-new.svg?auto=format&amp;amp;ixlib=react-9.0.3&amp;amp;h=40&amp;amp;w=132&amp;amp;q=50&amp;amp;dpr=2&quot; alt=&quot;hi-logo&quot; width=&quot;132&quot; style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Human Interest is on a mission to ensure that people in all lines of work have access to retirement benefits.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More than half of all working Americans are not saving enough for their future. Too often, it’s because they are employed by a company that doesn’t offer a retirement plan. Human Interest is changing that by making it affordable and accessible for small and medium-sized businesses to offer employees a path to financial independence through retirement savings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re a high-growth fintech company changing the retirement industry. We are backed by a number of investors. This includes funding from Marshall Wace and Baillie Gifford, as well as top investors such as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2023/01/13/2588448/0/en/Human-Interest-and-BlackRock-Join-Efforts-to-Expand-Access-to-Retirement-Plans-for-Working-Americans.html#:~:text=Human%20Interest%20has%20secured%20approximately%20%24500%20million%20in%20funding%20to%20date&amp;amp;text=NEW%20YORK%20and%20SAN%20FRANCISCO,businesses%20across%20the%20United%20States.&quot;&gt;BlackRock&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2021/08/04/2274611/0/en/The-Rise-Fund-Leads-200M-Series-D-Investment-in-Human-Interest-to-Accelerate-Growth-and-Societal-Impact.html&quot;&gt;TPG (The Rise Fund)&lt;/a&gt;, SoftBank, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2021/02/11/2174214/0/en/Human-Interest-Completes-105M-Series-C-Following-Breakout-Year-in-2020.html&quot;&gt;Glynn Capital&lt;/a&gt;, NewView Capital, USVP, Wing, Uncork, and more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the Benefits Processing Team, you will play a key role in managing participant distributions from their 401(k) accounts in a fast-paced and growing environment. Organized, detail-oriented, and adaptable, you will ensure accurate and timely processing of participant distributions while helping to refine and improve processes. You will gain in-depth knowledge of 401(k) systems and integrations to ensure distributions are processed correctly and on schedule. Your responsibilities will also include troubleshooting system issues, maintaining accurate records, and collaborating with internal teams to optimize workflows, track trends, and communicate key metrics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This team ensures the accuracy and integrity of customer accounts, preventing compliance issues and distribution delays. They maintain a smooth distribution system, ensuring customer satisfaction, and contribute reliable data for internal reporting and decision-making. By identifying inefficiencies and collaborating with other teams, they streamline workflows and reduce response times. The team regularly analyzes processes, offering insights for improvement and recommending tools or workflow adjustments. They uphold high-quality standards, ensuring projects are completed on time and within budget, supporting the company’s long-term success and operational goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you get to do every day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all data is carefully reviewed for accuracy, identifying and escalating discrepancies to maintain accurate and compliant customer accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consistently and promptly process participant distributions, meeting deadlines and ensuring distributions are correctly applied without delays.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pro

